f thomson leighton  wikipedia f thomson leighton from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search this biography of a living person needs additional citations for verification please help by adding reliable sources contentious material about living persons that is unsourced or poorly sourced must be removed immediately especially if potentially libelous or harmful january  learn how and when to remove this template message frank thomson leighton born  age – nationality american fields applied mathematics institutions massachusetts institute of technology akamai technologies alma mater princeton university massachusetts institute of technology doctoral advisor gary miller doctoral students peter shor mohammad hajiaghayi robert kleinberg frank thomson tom leighton is a professor of applied mathematics at the massachusetts institute of technology and the ceo of akamai technologies he has served as the head of the algorithms group at mits computer science and artificial intelligence laboratory since 996 and cofounded akamai with student daniel lewin in 998 he served on the presidential informational technology advisory committee pitac during which time he served as the chair of subcommittee on cybersecurity in 97 while a senior in high school he was named one of the westinghouse science talent search finalists now the intel sts going on to take home the nd place award behind eric lander now a colleague of leightons at mit leighton received his bse in electrical engineering from princeton university in 978 and his phd in mathematics from mit in 98 his brother david t leighton is a full professor at the university of notre dame specializing in transport phenomena he serves on the board of trustees of the society for science  the public ssp and of the center for excellence in education cee and he has participated in the distinguished lecture series at cees flagship program for high school students the research science institute rsi leightons father was a friend and navy colleague of rsi founder hyman g rickover contents  awards and honors  books  references  external links awards and honorsedit he was the first winner of the machtey award in 98 and is a fellow of the american academy of arts and sciences and a member of the national academy of engineering in 8 he was appointed as a member of the united states national academy of sciences in  he became a fellow of the american mathematical society he received the ieee computer society charles babbage award in  booksedit mathematics for computer science 7 by eric lehman f thomson leighton and albert r meyer introduction to parallel algorithms and architectures arrays trees hypercubes morgan kaufmann 99 isbn 5587 complexity issues in vlsi optimal layouts for the shuffleexchange graph and other networks mit press 98 isbn 6 referencesedit  erik nygren ramesh sitaraman and jennifer sun the akamai network a platform for highperformance internet applications acm sigops pdf operating systems review  july    dr tom leighton ceo  executive team akamaicom retrieved 79   david leighton — college of engineering engineeringndedu retrieved 79   list of fellows of the american mathematical society amsorg 5 retrieved 79  external linksedit find more aboutf thomson leightonat wikipedias sister projects media from commons texts from wikisource data from wikidata csail bio akamai bio authority control worldcat identities viaf 555 isni   557 85 sudoc 878 bnf cb55597 data mgp 75 retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlefthomsonleightonoldid78889 categories american computer scientiststheoretical computer scientistsliving peoplefellows of the american mathematical societyfellows of the society for industrial and applied mathematicsmembers of the united states national academy of engineeringmembers of the united states national academy of sciencesprinceton university alumnimassachusetts institute of technology alumnimassachusetts institute of technology facultythcentury american engineer